The Corporation has a robust process to monitor for indicators of potential impairment across its asset groups throughout the year.
This process is aligned with the requirements of ASC 360 and relies in part on the Corporation’s planning and budgeting cycle. In
2019, 2018 and 2017, the before-tax impairment charges were $0.1 billion, $0.7 billion and $2.0 billion, respectively.
