changes in tax law and tax rate. The Corporation’s results for 2018 include a $291 million tax credit, mainly in the Non-U.S.
Upstream, reflecting an updated estimate of the impact of U.S. tax reform including clarifications provided in tax regulations issued
by the U.S. Treasury. The Corporation completed its accounting for the enactment-date income tax effects of the U.S. Tax Cuts and
Jobs Act in accordance with Accounting Standard Codification Topic 740 (Income Taxes) during 2018.
